<p> <b><a name="Introduction:">Introduction:</a></b></p>
<p><font face="Verdana" size="2">Blacksmithing is probably the hardest trade
skill to learn, but it is most profitable when all is said and done. In beginning
blacksmithing expect to invest upwards of 175+ platinum to become an expert
(skill of 85 +). Then once your gain the rare and respected title of master
blacksmith, you will undoubtedly make your investment back as well as acquiring
a plentiful wealth stemming from your new career.</font></p>
<p><font face="Verdana" size="2">This
guide is one section:</font></p>
<ul>
  <li>
    <p><font face="Verdana" size="2"><a href="#Basic Blacksmithing:">Basic
    blacksmithing</a> will cover what you will need to do as a novice blacksmith
    (i.e. basic training, sharpening, making metal bits etc).</font></li>
</ul>
<p><font face="Verdana" size="2"><b><a name="Basic Blacksmithing:">Basic
Blacksmithing:</a></b></font></p>
<p> </p>
<p><font face="Verdana" size="2"><a name="What you need to do when you decide to become a smith:"><b>What
you need to do when you decide to become a smith:</b></a></font></p>
<p> </p>
<p><font face="Verdana" size="2">When
you decide to become a blacksmith, the very first thing you must do is invest at
least 20 practice points into your blacksmith skill. It is <a href="http://www.everlore.com">Everlore</a>'s
policy in all trade to invest at least 10 practice in most all skills but because
blacksmithing is a very expensive trade to learn we recommend 20 simply to save
you money time, and components (ore and bits etc). This should give you a pretty
solid base on which to build your career as a blacksmith. After you train in
blacksmithing the next thing you should do is purchase the basic blacksmithing
book, (note: there are 2 buy the one labeled "Basic Blacksmithing" for
now). In this guide we will include the whole text of both blacksmithing books
but it is rumored by "<a href="mailto:evanl@obsidian-tech.com">Trindalc</a>" of Fennin Ro that:</font></p>
<p> </p>
<p><i><font face="Verdana" size="2">"If
you buy the blacksmith books and keep them visible in your inventory while you
smith (not in a back pack etc), then it will greatly increase your chances of </font></i><font face="Verdana" size="2"><i>success."</i></font></p>
<p> </p>
<p><font face="Verdana" size="2">So
we recommend you do this, again to save you money and time. </font></p>
<ul>
  <li>
    <p><font face="Verdana" size="2">Here
    is a picture of the what "<i>Basic Blacksmithing</i>" looks
    like:            <img border="0" src="http://www.everlore.com/files2/Book.jpg" align="center" width="49" height="49"></font></li>
</ul>
<p><font face="Verdana" size="2">And
here is the an excerpt from the text of the "<i>Basic Blacksmithing
Book":</i></font></p>
<p> </p>
<p align="center"><font face="Verdana" size="2"><i>"<a name="Guide to Blacksmithing TxT">Guide
to Blacksmithing</a></i></font></p>
<p align="center"> </p>
<p align="center"><i><font face="Verdana" size="2">Blacksmithing
is the art of creating tools from primal elements of the earth - Ore, Water, and
Fire.</font></i> <i><font face="Verdana" size="2">Talented blacksmiths can
create weapons, armor, and other useful items. Before
you undertake your work as a smith, you will need a forge. Forges can be found
in most cites. Place you raw materials upon the forge. Begin your work. </font></i></p>
<p align="center"> </p>
<p align="center"><i><font face="Verdana" size="2">Conversion
rates:</font></i></p>
<p align="center"> </p>
<p align="center"><i><font face="Verdana" size="2">Two
pieces of Small ore = Metal Bits</font></i></p>
<p align="center"><i><font face="Verdana" size="2">Three
pieces of Small bricks of ore = Large Brick of ore</font></i></p>
<p align="center"><i><font face="Verdana" size="2">Three
large bricks or ore = Block of ore</font></i></p>
<p align="center"> </p>
<p align="center"><i><font face="Verdana" size="2">You
will need a flask of water to cool the ore."</font></i></p>
<p> </p>
<p><font size="2" face="Verdana">The
content of the rest of the book is included in "<a name="Basic Blacksmiths Recipes:" href="#Basic Blacksmiths Recipes:">Basic
Blacksmith Recipe</a>" book below. </font></p>
<p><font face="Verdana" size="2">Now
the last step before smithing your first item, will be to gather some basic materials
used in basic smithing and to find a <a href="#Forge">forge</a> (but luckily this
is usually very near to where you find a merchant that sells basic smithing
materials). But first you need to know what you will be doing, so that you know
what to buy.</font></p>
<p align="center"><a href="#Blacksmithing:">Top</a></p>
<p> </p>
<p><font face="Verdana" size="2"><b><a name="What to do first">Basic
Smithing</a></b></font></p>
<p> </p>
<p><font face="Verdana" size="2">The
first thing you will be doing is making metal bits, sharpening rusty weapons and
making studs.</font></p>
<ol>
  <li>
    <p><font face="Verdana" size="2">Making
    Metal Bits: Metal bits are the most basic metal item and will be a building
    block for many other metal items. In order to make them you will need to buy
    small pieces of ore and flasks of water. Buy both items in bulk because you
    will probably be making many metal bits. Then find your local forge. </font></li>
</ol>
<p>                   
<font face="Verdana" size="2"><i>Note on <a href="#Forge">Forges</a>: Forges are located in most major cites. But
we recommend for really serious smiths to go to Freeport to begin your Smithing
career. For it has the best blacksmithing resources and a couple of forges. One
is located in north Freeport the other in south Freeport. Note: Some Armor can
be only made by certain races which means you can only use the forges in those
cities. Check the Guides for Race Blacksmithing. </i></font></p>
<p>Forges
look like
this:</p>
<p><div align=center><table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	<tr>
		<td align=center><a name="http://www.everlore.com/files2/Forge">
			<img border="0" src="http://www.everlore.com/files2/Forge1.jpg" width="250" height="328"></a>
		</td>
		<td align=center>
			<img border="0" src="http://www.everlore.com/files2/Froge2.jpg" width="250" height="259">
		</td>
	</tr></table>	
<font face="Verdana" size="2">When you have all the necessary items, go up to the forge and left click on
it, place in the window that appears 2 small pieces ore and 1 flask of water.
Then press the "Combine" button that is at the bottom of the window.
And of you succeed than metal bits will be placed into your inventory if not you
will lose the ore and the water. Important do not put items in stacked! It will
not work and you will always lose your components when there are stacked. Make a
lot of metal bits, and do not sell them  back to merchants. You will need
them later on.</font>
<p> </p>
<p>   <font face="Verdana" size="2">
2.   Sharpening rusty weapons: This will be skill building exercise.
To Sharpen anything first you need to get a sharpening stone, and a rusty item
to sharpen. This can be rusty weapons you get off the corpses of your slain victims
while out hunting or you can attempt to sharpen items for other people. When you
have both a sharpen stone and a rusty item, go to your <a href="#Forge">forge</a>
open it (by left clicking on it)</font></p>
<p><font face="Verdana" size="2">and
place both the stone and the weapon inside. Press the combine button at the bottom
and if you succeed than the weapon will be placed back into your inventory, only
it will no longer be rusty. It will be tarnished. If you fail in your attempt
your sharpening stone will be the only thing to disappear.</font></p>
<p> </p>
<p>   <font face="Verdana" size="2">
3.    Now that you have brought your skill up a little with the
above practices and piled up a small collection of metal bits, you are ready to
make studs (your first real money returning item) and files. </font></p>
<p><font face="Verdana" size="2">To
make a files you must buy a file mold. These can be bought at venders that sell
blacksmithing molds. Once you have some molds, go back to the forge and combine
them with 1 metal bit, and 1 flask of water. </font></p>
<p><font face="Verdana" size="2">To
make studs combine in the forge a file, a flask of water, and 3 metal bits. You
should not attempt studs until your blacksmith skill is at least 25 - 30. You
will make the most profit selling studs to <a href="http://www.everlore.com/skills/default.asp?mode=5&id=602">tailors</a>.</font></p>
<p align="center"><a href="#Blacksmithing:">Top</a></p>
<p> </p>
<p><b><a name="Your Career as a young Blacksmith:">Your
Career as a young Blacksmith:</a></b></p>
<p> </p>
<p><font face="Verdana" size="2">To
make all the items in the basic blacksmithing book, follow the same procedure as
the above items. Collect the needed components and "Combine" them in
the <a href="#Forge">forge</a>. Allot of the items that you can create are
needed by other trade skills. So a good way initially to make back some of your
investment is to bard out your skill making items on demand for the people who
need them.</font></p>
<p> </p>
<p><font face="Verdana" size="2"><b><a name="General Blacksmithing Guide">General
Blacksmithing Guide:</a></b></font></p>
<p> </p>
  <p><font face="Verdana" size="2">These
  are just about every General Blacksmithing Items that can be made up to date
  not including Class armor and weapons that can be made which can be found in
  our Guide to all Class Armor.</font></p>
<p><o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
