	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Hear ye, Hear ye, a master smith of skill 130 to help ye fledgling smiths.<BR>
 First of all, i smithed in Halas, Qeynos and Erudin. Erudin was the closest place to buy ore, and i chose my Shaman to buy my smith in part because of her high WIS(which increases your chance of successfully making an item) and since she could gate back to Qeynos as molds ARE NOT sold in Erudin. ARRGH!!!  I found that the quickest way was to stay in Erudin and make about 160 metal bits at a time. I DID NOT train my skill, and just made metal bits-2 small PIECES of ore(they are stackable), and 1 flask of water- from the start until trivial at 21, since you need so many.  After metal bits, i made scalers until 41-which are 1 metal bits, 1 flask of water, and a scaler mold-at which point they became trivial.  AFter scalers, it was lanterns-1 metal bits, 1 flask of water, 1 bottle, 1 lantern casing mold-until 68.  Then i moved onto skewers-1 metal bit, 1 flask of water, 1 skewer mold-which got me from 68-115.  Even though at 100, u can start making banded, I WOULD STRONGLY suggest you NOT try and make banded, because the failures eat up any profit you would make, and it takes FOREVER to advance your skill this way.  From 115-122, i made pots-1 metal bits, 1 flask of water, 1 standing legs mold, and a pot mold. AT this point i started to safely make banded, and make a profit which i have continued doing up to my current skill of 130.<BR>
<BR>
  WARNING: Blacksmithing IS NOT A POOR MAN'S SKILL!!! To get to a skill of 130, I invested about 250pp, but have now made about 120pp back from selling banded.  Much of my smithing occured in Halas, as i didn't have to zone to get my molds as much as i would in Qeynos.  Everybody says go to FreePort to be a smith, but i did just dandy in Halas and Erudin, gate helps EXTREMELY for not having to wait for the boat to get off of Erudin.  I know that Studs and Steel Boning, both of use to tailors are in HIGH HIGH demand around Qeynos from the lack of smiths.  Well, good luck to ye aspiring smiths, and I am always willing to help if you are on Lanys T'Vyl.<BR>
<BR>
good luck to ye all<BR>
<BR>
Henorma, Shaman of the 12th Season, Lanys T'Vyl<BR>
Master Smith (130)<BR>
Newbie Tailor (20)
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
